Package ccre.channel

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BooleanInput
    A BooleanInput is a way to get the current state of a boolean input, and to subscribe to notifications of changes in the boolean input's value.
    BooleanInputPoll
    A BooleanInputPoll is a way to get the current state of a boolean input.
    BooleanOutput
    A BooleanOutput is an interface for anything that can be turned on or off.
    EventInput
    An event input or source.
    EventOutput
    An event output or consumer.
    FloatInput
    A FloatInput is a way to get the current state of a float input, and to subscribe to notifications of changes in the float input's value.
    FloatInputPoll
    A FloatInputPoll is a way to get the current state of a float input.
    FloatOutput
    A FloatOutput is an interface for anything that can be set to an analog value.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BooleanFilter
    A BooleanFilter is a wrapper that can be wrapped around any kind of Output, Input, InputPoll, or InputProducer, and will apply the same transformation in any case.
    BooleanStatus
    A virtual node that is both a BooleanOutput and a BooleanInput.
    EventLogger
    An event that logs a string at a LogLevel when fired.
    EventStatus
    An implementation of an EventInput.
    FloatFilter
    A FloatFilter is a wrapper that can be wrapped around any kind of Output, Input, InputPoll, or InputProducer, and will apply the same transformation in any case.
    FloatStatus
    A virtual node that is both a FloatOutput and a FloatInput.
